Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF) Healthwatch stores and visualizes recommended key operational metrics from core PCF components, including bosh-reported VM metrics, to help Operators better understand the current health, performance, and capacity of a given PCF Foundation. PCF Healthwatch also creates measures of operational value via recommended continuous validation tests and contextually derived metrics; forwarding these product-specific measures into the firehose for existing customer solutions to pick up as desired.

## <a id='features'></a>Key Features

PCF Healthwatch includes the following key features:

* Offers an opinionated PCF Operational Monitoring dashboard, providing coverage of the recommended [Key Performance Indicators](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/1-11/monitoring/kpi.html) and [Key Scaling Indications](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/1-11/monitoring/key-cap-scaling.html) for a given version of PCF. Associated data is currently retained for 25 hours. 
* Executes recommended operational health checks as continuous validation tests, storing and displaying results, as well as [forwarding](using.html#firehose) result data into the firehose for consumption by existing firehose consumers. 

